////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
///////////// GUIDE ON HOW TO RUN FADCcom command /////////
//////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////


in directory replay/scripts/FADC_decode_apex/

./FADCcom #run_number #maxEvent #spectrometer


where:

	#run_number is the number of the run to be replayed (looks for apex files)

	#maxEvents is the number of events to be replayd

	#spectrometer can be: 'LHRS' or 'RHRS' (without quotaion marks)
		      
		      this selects ROC31 to be analyzed for 'LHRS' or
		      ROC20 to be analyzed for 'RHRS'


	

This scripts produces differently named output root files for LHRS or RHRS, so 
you won't delete previous output.

(relevant log entry:  https://logbooks.jlab.org/entry/3644907)